---
// Sveltia CMS admin — a single static page, no server. The bundle is copied from
// node_modules into public/sveltia/ by the sync-cms script (see package.json); the
// content model lives in public/sveltia/config.yml. (The assets deliberately do NOT
// live under public/admin/ — a public directory sharing this route's path makes the
// dev server answer /admin with a 404 status.)
//
// Editing works two ways:
//  - locally: `pnpm site cms`, open /admin, "Work with Local Repository" (Chrome/Edge),
//    pick the repo folder — saves write straight into the working tree.
//  - hosted (later): GitHub backend sign-in needs a small token-exchange service
//    (sveltia-cms-auth); decided together with the deploy target.
---

<html lang="nl">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
    <title>CMS — schakl.</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <link rel="cms-config-url" type="application/yaml" href="/sveltia/config.yml" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <script is:inline src="/sveltia/sveltia-cms.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
